The author expresses their outrage and pain over the video of Tyre Nichols' beating, which resulted in his death. They acknowledge the fear and trauma that Black and Brown Americans experience daily. They offer condolences to Nichols' family and call for peaceful protests. The author spoke with Nichols' mother and stepfather and emphasizes the need for a thorough investigation. They believe that real change can only happen by preventing such tragedies and mention their efforts to improve accountability in law enforcement through executive orders and legislation.